name: Digits
statement: Input The first line contains a single integer $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \le t \le 32$$$) — the number of test cases. Each test case contains $$$n$$$ lines. The $$$i$$$-th line contains an integer $$$a_i$$$ ($$$1 \le a_i \le 9$$$). The sum of $$$n$$$ over all test cases doesn't exceed $$$155$$$. Output For each test case, print one integer — the answer. Example Input 3 2 1 4 7 1 2 3 5 Output 8 7 30
inputFormat: The first line contains a single integer $$$t$$$ ($$$1 \le t \le 32$$$) — the number of test cases. Each test case contains $$$n$$$ lines. The $$$i$$$-th line contains an integer $$$a_i$$$ ($$$1 \le a_i \le 9$$$). The sum of $$$n$$$ over all test cases doesn't exceed $$$155$$$.
outputFormat: For each test case, print one integer — the answer.
